XII

CICERO To LUCIUS AEMILIUS PAULLUS, CONSUL ELECT

Between Iconium and Cybistra, September, 51 B.c.

Although I never had any doubt that the people of l

Rome, in consideration of your magnificent services to the Republic, and the highly influential position of your family, would elect you consul with the greatest enthusiasm and unanimity of voting‚ I had yet a thrill of inconceivable joy when the news reached me ; and I pray the gods to prosper your high office, and that you may administer it in a manner befitting your own and your ancestors’ position.

And would that I had been able to be on the spot and see that eagerly desired day, and in return for all your splendid devotion and kindness to me to render you my aid and active support !
